        "id": 8341
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-12-04T17:56:25Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "At some point in the past, the behavior of unclipped layers with subsequent replace-ops drifted from what this test was expecting. On a single SkCanvas with an unclipped layer, we punch a clipRegion-difference hole in the prior layer. However, then the replace op is sent to every top-level device, which erases this hole.\n\nThe SkCanvasStack that is used for the canvas-state rendering to simulate a device stack explicitly re-applies the hole punching after ever clip operation, so we get divergent behavior.\n\nSince expanding clip ops are going away, and because unclipped layers have basically gone away (next CL), I figured I\u0027d just change this test to pass.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 227,
        "startChar": 37,
        "endLine": 227,
        "endChar": 61
      },
